Claims Claims 1. An encoding method comprising: - encoding (S120) a picture part in a bitstream and reconstructing (S120) said picture part; - determining (S130) refinement data such that: - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between an original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part after refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part without refinement in the case where no mapping applies before coding; - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between an original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part after inverse mapping and refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part after inverse mapping without refinement in the case where mapping applies before coding and said refinement is out of the decoding loop; - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between a mapped original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part after refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said mapped original version of said picture part and said reconstructed picture part without refinement in the case where mapping applies before coding and said refinement is in the decoding loop; and - encoding (S140) said refinement data in said bitstream. 2. The encoding method according to claim 1, further comprising refining said reconstructed picture part with said determined refinement data before storing said refined picture part in a reference picture buffer in the case where said refinement is in the decoding loop. 3. The encoding method according to claim 1 or 2, wherein refining said reconstructed picture part with said refinement data is performed for one color component of said picture part independently of any other color component of said picture part. 4. The encoding method according to claim 1 or 2, wherein refining said reconstructed picture part with said refinement data for one color component of said picture part depends on another color component of said picture part. 5. The encoding method according to any one of claims 1 to 4, wherein encoding said refinement data in said bitstream comprises encoding for at least one color component N refinement values, N being an integer, said N refinement values defining pivot points of a piecewise-linear function. 6. The encoding method according to any one of claims 1 to 5, wherein said reconstructed picture part is said reconstructed picture part obtained after in-loop filtering. 7. A decoding method comprising: - decoding (S220, S230) a picture part and refinement data from a bitstream, the refinement data having been derived during encoding such that: - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between an original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part after refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part without refinement in the case where no mapping applies before coding; - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between an original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part after inverse mapping and refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part after inverse mapping without refinement in the case where mapping applies before coding and said refinement is out of the decoding loop; 

 - a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between a mapped original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part after refinement by said refinement data is decreased compared to a rate distortion cost computed as a weighted sum of data coding cost and of a distortion between said mapped original version of said picture part and said decoded picture part without refinement in the case where mapping applies before coding and said refinement is in the decoding loop; and - refining (S240) the decoded picture part with the decoded refinement data. 8. The decoding method according to claim 7, further comprising inverse mapping said decoded picture part and wherein refining with the decoded refinement data is applied on the decoded picture part after inverse mapping. 9. The decoding method according to claim 7, wherein refining said decoded picture part with said decoded refinement data is done before storing said refined decoded picture part in a reference picture buffer in the case where said refinement is in the decoding loop. 10. The decoding method according to any one of claims 7 to 9, wherein refining said decoded picture part with said refinement data is performed for one color component of said picture part independently of any other color component of said picture part. 11. The decoding method according to any one of claims 7 to 9, wherein refining said decoded picture part with said refinement data for one color component of said picture part depends on another color component of said picture part. 12. The decoding method according to any one of claims 7 to 11, wherein decoding said refinement data from said bitstream comprises decoding for at least one color component, N refinement values, N being an integer, said N refinement values defining pivot points of a piecewise-linear function. 13. The decoding method according to any one of claims 7 to 11, wherein said decoded picture part is said decod